On 04/04/21, around 11 AM, the customer walked in for his COVID vaccine appointment.  After registering for the vaccine , the patient sat in the designated area and one of our immunizing technicians administered the vaccine while I was observing and I left the immunization area while my technician was finishing up cleaning. When the patient asked the immunizing technician a question about side effects, she offered him to talk to the pharmacist at the consultation window. While I was assisting the next customer, I heard a loud sound and saw the customer collapsing on the floor. I ran outside and checked his pulse, and asked to call 911. He was conscious and breathing. I went inside the pharmacy to get EpiPen and informed the customer that I will be administering EpiPen, but he denied it. In the meantime, the immunizing technician was already on hold with 911 and informed that they are on the way. The customers in the waiting area also kept him engaged and were watching him if he is alert. The store manager on duty was also in the pharmacy area. I came inside the pharmacy and offered the patient a chair to sit in. Paramedics arrived in a few minutes to transport him to the hospital. The patient came back to the pharmacy around 2:30PM to collect his immunization card and when I inquired about how he is doing, the patient informed me that he is feeling more better and the ER determined that there was no allergic reaction to the vaccine but the patient most likely stood up too quickly after the vaccine was administered.

March 26, 2021: One week to the day after receiving my second dose of the Pfizer COVID19 vaccine, my right eye suddenly had double vision and facial pain behind the right eye and all around the right eye (forehead, right temple, around to under the right eye on the cheek).  The right eye would not move correctly.    March 27, 2021: I went to see Optometrist.  He performed an eye exam with dilation and stated that the right eye was slow to track, and that the nerve behind the right eye was inflamed.  He recommended blood work, CT scan, and an MRI.    March 27, 2021 ? March 28, 2021: We went to ER at 9:00pm.  After waiting six hours, I finally was able to see an ER doctor.  No medical history was taken.  No bloodwork was done.  ER Dr performed a CT scan as Dr requested.  CT scan w/o contrast showed no masses or hemorrhages.  ER suggested to follow-up with Nuerology.  March 29, 2021: Went to Neurologist and he examined me.  He called in another Dr for a second opinion.  They stated that it may be a possible cranial nerve palsy and ordered multiple MRIs.    March 29, 2021: The earliest MRI appointment available was April 7, 2021.  Scheduled the MRI.  April 1, 2021: Had blood drawn at lab as Dr requested.  April 2, 2021: Two weeks from the day of COVID19 vaccine #2, my right eyelid would not open at all and the pain was getting worse.  April 5, 2021: Went to ER at 4:30am.  Triage nurse sent me straight to an ER room and within minutes an ER doctor was there.  Within 15 minutes after seeing the ER doctor, a Neurologist was examining me.  The nuero doctor was very thorough.  While waiting for the MRI, other neurologists and residents also examined me.  MRI scans with and without contrast were performed.  MRI images were clear ? no tumors, no aneurisms, and no stroke.  They concluded that it was a micro-vascular injury to cranial nerve #3.  (Similar to the Bells Palsy that I had in 2015.)  They prescribed gabapentin to help calm the nerve pain.  Follow-up will be with nuero-ophthalmologist.

heart attack; This initial spontaneous report was received from a lawyer regarding a case in litigation and refers to a female patient of unknown age. No information was provided regarding medical history, concurrent conditions, or concomitant medications. In or around 27-OCT-2014, the patient was inoculated with zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX) (lot#, expiration date, dose, dose# and route not specified) for routine health maintenance and for its intended purpose: the prevention of shingles (herpes zoster). Shortly after receiving zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX) vaccine, the patient suffered a heart attack. As a result of these symptoms, the patient was seen and treated by medical providers and was still under their care. As a direct and proximate result of zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX) vaccine, the patient's symptoms had resulted in physical limitations not present prior to using zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX). The patient also experienced mental and emotional distress due to resulting physical limitations and seriousness of condition. As a result of the manufacture, marketing, advertising, promotion, distribution and/or sale of zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX), the patient sustained severe and permanent personal injuries. Further, the patient suffered serious, progressive, permanent, and incurable injuries, as well as significant conscious pain and suffering, mental anguish, emotional distress, loss of enjoyment of life, physical impairment and injury. As a direct and proximate result of zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX), the patient had suffered and incurred damages, including medical expenses; the loss of accumulations; and other economic and non-economic damages. The outcome of the event of heart attack was considered to be not recovered and causal relationship was assessed as related.   The lawyer considered the event of heart attack to be disability.  Upon internal review, the event of heart attack was determined to be medically significant.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I got a rash like symptom, it looked like mosquito bites ALL OVER  my legs and arms. It itches A LOt and ends up red when I scratch. It ended up actually worsening so I went to urgent care and was told that my immune system was just reacting to vaccine. I was prescribed a stronger benadryl .

About 20 minutes after vaccination, started to feel tingly sensation in mouth, tongue.  About 1 hour after vaccination my lips felt numb.  No blue lips, no rash/hive, no swelling of tongue, lips or face, no difficulty breathing or swallowing.  Just numbness in lips and tingling feeling on tongue, all over mouth.   The numbness felt like novacaine shot you would get if you were getting dental work done.  Numbness in lips lasted about 3 hours but gradually reduced to just tingling feeling after.  The tingling feeling in my mouth gradually got better every hour after that.  It still lasted all night.  It did not completely go away until the next morning.  After the morning, numbness and tingling sensation went away.

Muscle pain and muscle spasms starting in neck and on entire back all the way down to lower back lasted 7 days with consistent improvement with each passing day; treated with Tylenol. Splotchy red rash on arms and part of legs, accompanied by pins and needles feeling in majority of body. Treated as an allergic reaction since symptoms were same as those from allergic reaction to Zofran. Treated with hydroxyzine and Benadryl; resolved in 24 hours. Chills causing entire body to shake lasted approximately 1 1/2 hours and resolved suddenly on its own. Feeling feverish and verified by checking temperature for 3 days after vaccination, starting day after vaccination; took Tylenol. Pain at injection site was almost same as for any other vaccination, just a bit more.
ALLERGIES: Penicillin, Neosporin, Azithromycin, Reglan, Zofran, dairy, cat.

A consumer reported that, "arm being a little sore" (PT: Pain in extremity), "woke up in a fog and have not been able to shake it" (PT: Feeling abnormal), "feeling very low energy" (PT: Asthenia),"lethargic" (PT: Lethargy), "feel very tired" (PT: Fatigue), and "injection site was just a little sore" (PT: Injection site pain) following the immunisation with BioThrax (anthrax vaccine adsorbed). On 11FEB2021, the patient received first dose of BioThrax injection in the arm. On the same day, the patient had little soreness in the arm. Next morning, the patient woke up in a fog and was not able to shake it. Despite of 7-8 hours of sleep, the patient felt very tired like he got an hour of sleep only. The patient felt lethargic with very low energy but no fever or body aches. The patient stated that the injection site was about what he was expecting, just a little sore. The outcome of the reported events was unknown at the time of report.  Company Comments: A consumer received first dose of BioThrax and on the same day developed injection site pain, arm was little sore (pain in extremity), and the next day the consumer was feeling abnormal with fatigue, lethargy, and asthenia even after having 7 to 8 hours of sleep. Further details of the events is limited. Injection site pain, pain in extremity, and fatigue are known effects of BioThrax, and the causality of these events is assessed as possible. Considering the case information, the causality of lethargy, asthenia, and feeling abnormal is assessed as possible with BioThrax.  Follow up information received from the consumer on 03MAR2021 which included time of administration of BioThrax, address of the reporter, gender of the consumer, date of birth, treatment medications, and outcome of the events.  It was updated that the male patient was administered BioThrax injection at 3 pm.   It was updated that all his symptoms last for about 24-36 hours, except for the sore arm which was persisted for 3 days. On 12-Feb-2021, his symptoms were resolved by 9 pm, except for the sore arm which lasted for three days. He used ibuprofen and Tylenol (paracetamol) for sore arm.  Company Comment: A consumer received first dose of BioThrax and on the same day developed injection site pain, arm was little sore (pain in extremity), and the next day the consumer was feeling abnormal with fatigue, lethargy, and asthenia even after having 7 to 8 hours of sleep. All events resolved within 24 to 36 hours except for pain in extremity which resolved after three days after taking tylenol and ibuprofen. The patient's medical history was not provided. Concomitant product use was not provided by the reporter.  On 03-MAR-2021, prior to the onset of the events, the patient received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (Batch number: unknown) intramuscularly in the left arm for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection.   On 03-MAR-2021around 15:00, she received the Moderna COVID-19 vaccine in her left deltoid muscle at Shop Rite Pharmacy. 6 hours later she noticed red scratch marks all over her upper body, her heart beat was getting very rapid, her breathing was labored, her vision was wonky, her right eye was swollen and her face was beat red. 911 was called, upon arrival the EMT administered IV diphenhydramine (Benadryl) 50 mg and at the emergency room they gave her famotidine (Pepcid) and a steroid drip (methylprednisolone). After receiving treatment, the reporter states the patient felt great and was discharged. The doctor prescribed her methylprednisolone. Additionally she states the patient was also nauseous last night which went away around 2:00am. They told her to consult her primary care provider about the second Moderna COVID-19 vaccination  Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the event(s) was not provided/unknown.  The outcome of the event, serious allergic reaction is unknown.; Reporter's Comments: This case concerns a 21 Y/O F with serious unexpected events of hypersensitivity, dyspnea, and nonserious unexpected heart rate increased, vision blurred, eye swelling, erythema, scratches and expected nausea. Event onset on Day 1 after first dose mRNA-1273. Treated with diphenhydramine and methylprednisolone. Hypersensitivity resolved. SYMPTOM_TEXT: Experience exact symptoms of Covid19 virus as when I had it in Dec/2020. nausea, fever, cough, and body aches. It lasted 24 hours.

4 hours after the vaccine shot on my left arm, my left eye started twitching.  It happened a lot at first, and happened multiple times a day for 10-20 minutes at a time.  After a couple weeks it slowed down to the point where it only happens every couple days.  This absolutely did not happen before that exact day so I am relatively sure it was caused by the vaccine.
Pain Lump/swelling on neck (left side) Lump/swelling on Armpit (left hand) Constant pain
Flu like symptoms,  SEVERE  muscle cramps. Loss of feeling in limbs. Headache and nausea. Lightheaded. Chills and shaking.
currently in hospital (ICU). Fainting, lightheadedness, extreme fatigue, petechiae, extremely low platelet count, possibly kidney damage, nose bleed, weakness,

Went to get up to get ready for work and instantly collapsed-scraping up knee. Became extremely nauseous, weak, excruciating headache and dizzy. Unable to stand, had to crawl to nearby chair and call for wife. Thought might be dehydrated, extremely pale, tried to drink water, but began vomiting. BP was elevated, but no temperature. Tried to eat crackers and drink more water, but continued to violently vomit. Never felt so badly in entire life. No strength to stand or get up the stairs to be taken to ER, so had to call paramedics. When they arrived, BP had come down, but they felt needed to be transported to ER, so they took to healthcare facility at about 1:30 pm.
LAB_DATA: EKG's-paramedics performed at home, and repeated in hospital, all pretty normal. Bloodwork and urine tests all run at hospital and were pretty much normal. Doctor determined the cause for sudden illness to be a reaction from second dose of PFizer vaccine, given approximately 17 hours prior to beginning of symptoms noticed. Was released from ER on 4/02/21, and have been unable to return to work. More strength and no further vomiting, but severe headache and dizziness has continued, along with the fatigue and some nausea.
OTHER_MEDS: Nexium, Hydroxyzine, Zyrtec, men's daily vitamin

Autoimmune Hemolytic Anemia; Bell's Palsy; Information has been received from a lawyer concerning a case in litigation and refers to a patient of unknown age and gender. In or around October 29, 2012, patient was inoculated with zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX) (dose, route of administration, lot # and expiration date were not reported) for routine health maintenance and for its intended purpose: the prevention of shingles (herpes zoster). Shortly after receiving zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX), patient suffered severe symptoms of fatigue, dizziness, jaundice, and a syncope episode he also had very dark urine and was diagnosed with sudden onset of autoimmune hemolytic anemia. Patient additionally suffered right side facial paralysis and was diagnosed with Bell's Palsy. As a direct and proximate result of zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX) vaccine, patient's symptoms have resulted in physical limitations not present prior to using the product. Patient also experiences mental and emotional distress due to resulting physical limitations and seriousness of his condition. As a result of the manufacture, marketing, advertising, promotion, distribution and/or sale of zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX), patient sustained severe and permanent personal injuries. Further, as a tragic consequence of company's wrongful conduct, patient suffered serious, progressive, permanent, and incurable injuries, as well as significant conscious pain and suffering, mental anguish, emotional distress, loss of enjoyment of life, physical impairment and injury. As a direct and proximate result of company's conduct, patient has suffered and incurred damages, including medical expenses; the loss of accumulations; and other economic and non-economic damages. The outcome of the events was unknown. The events were considered to be related to zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX).     Upon internal review, the events of autoimmune hemolytic anemia and Bell's Palsy were considered to be medically significant.

Collapsed on the floor at her home and was transported to the hospital; Diagnosed with Guillain-Barre Syndrome; Is a quadriplegic at this time / cannot move her arms or legs; Is a quadriplegic at this time / cannot move her arms or legs; Breathing difficulty; Recurrent UTI's during her hospital stay; Treated for pneumonia; This case was reported by a consumer via call center representative and described the occurrence of passed out in a 77-year-old female patient who received Herpes zoster (Shingrix) for prophylaxis.   On 13th March 2021, the patient received the 1st dose of Shingrix (intramuscular). On 20th March 2021, 7 days after receiving Shingrix, the patient experienced passed out (serious criteria hospitalization, disability, GSK medically significant and life threatening), guillain barre syndrome (serious criteria hospitalization, disability, GSK medically significant and life threatening), quadriplegia (serious criteria hospitalization, disability, GSK medically significant and life threatening) and mobility decreased (serious criteria hospitalization, disability, GSK medically significant and life threatening). On 2nd April 2021, the patient experienced pneumonia (serious criteria hospitalization, disability, GSK medically significant and life threatening) and urinary tract infection (serious criteria hospitalization, disability and life threatening). On an unknown date, the patient experienced difficulty breathing (serious criteria hospitalization, disability and life threatening). The patient was treated with immunoglobulins nos (Ivig) and operations and procedures (Plasmapheresis (Nos)). On an unknown date, the outcome of the passed out was unknown and the outcome of the guillain barre syndrome, quadriplegia, pneumonia and mobility decreased were not recovered/not resolved and the outcome of the difficulty breathing was recovered/resolved and the outcome of the urinary tract infection was recovering/resolving.   It was unknown if the reporter considered the passed out, guillain barre syndrome, quadriplegia, pneumonia, difficulty breathing, urinary tract infection and mobility decreased to be related to Shingrix.  Additional details were provided as follows: The case was reported by the patient's daughter. The patient received the Shingrix vaccine into her right arm.  Exactly one week later, on 20th March 2021, the patient collapsed on the floor at her home and was transported to the hospital.  Eight hours after arriving at the hospital the patient was intubated.  A stroke was ruled out by magnetic resonance Imaging and computerized tomography scans.  The patient was on IVIG (intravenous immunoglobulins) therapy starting 20th March 2021 for 5 days with no improvement.  On 26th March 2021, the neurologist started plasmapheresis therapy and the patient started showing signs of improvement by being able to move her toes.  The patient was diagnosed with Guillain-Barre Syndrome and was a quadriplegic at the time of reporting.   The intubation tube was removed on 2nd April 2021 and then was able to breath on her own.  The patient was treated for pneumonia on the same day.  The reporter stated that her mother was able to speak and eat solid food, could also move her fingers and hold a pencil but could not move her arms or legs as of 7th April 2021. The patient also had been treated for recurrent urinary tract infections during her hospital stay. The reporter did not give permission to contact the healthcare professional, but she did give a permission to contact her on behalf of her mother. The reporter asked for the address and fax number of GlaxoSmithKline Legal Department, which was provided to her. She inquired how long it would take to hear from legal department and was informed that she would be contacted within 6 to 8 weeks.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Around five hours after shot I felt what I would describe as brain fog and light headache, by the evening I was aching, chilling and had 101 fever. I am the only one with the fainting spells. Still feel fatigued today. And shoulders and left arm injection site still sore and achy.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I contracted pink eye and was treated with steroid drops around the same time as my shot. I believe it was 02/10 when my first pink eye symptoms appeared. My mother and son also had it a week prior so I was not alarmed. However, since then, I've been diagnosed with uveitis after the pink eye infection cleared, and have had continuous issues with extreme dry eye and vision changes. My eye doctor is thinking potentially an autoimmune issue, I'm seeing the diagnostic clinic to hopefully uncover this, but I've never had such eye issues before. I've had some eye fatigue that affected my vision in college due to sleep deprivation, but nothing like this. The chronic pain I'm dealing with has been worsened. This could be autoimmune and a random event, or it could be autoimmune undiagnosed that was trigger by the vaccine, or it could be just the vaccine. But since I believe in medicine and vaccines, I believe it is my duty to report the potential issue so that others and research could benefit from my experience should this be related.

Opthalmologist follow up: 04-09 extreme dryness and vision changes
CUR_ILL: Pink Eye developed around the same time of the vaccine. My mother and son had it a week prior to me receiving the first vaccine.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: On April 4, 2021, my mother, was diagnosed with a cerebral venous sinus thrombosis (CVST).  I figured I would report this, as I am seeing more and more reports about the vaccines tied to this rare brain blood clot:   "Moderna?s rival mRNA shot has been linked to five CVST cases out of 4 million vaccinated." "More than a dozen countries worldwide temporarily stopped administering the Oxford-AstraZeneca COVID vaccine, notes the Association of American Physicians and Surgeons (AAPS), because of deaths from blood clotting disorders, with either clots or excessive bleeding. Some patients experienced the extremely rare event of clots in the veins that drain blood from the brain (venous sinus thrombosis)."
LAB_DATA: Prothrombin II Genetic Mutation discovered after blood test on April 5, 2021 (at least three out of her seven sisters also have this mutation). "There are probably predisposing factors, but AAPS notes there is at present no way to screen for this in advance."
OTHER_MEDS: Atorvastatin; Vitamin D and Zinc supplements

I had no appetite that evening. By 8pm, I had a 101.0 fever, and by 9:30pm the cramps were severe in my lower stomach. The shot was at a drive up event at a University.. After chugging the ginger ale I felt a bit better and was given the  ok to leave after 15 minutes. Back at work, I felt  better but still just a bit  ? off?.  But this passed in an hour and I was good the rest of the day. It could be possible that the shot caused some lower blood pressure immediately or within the hour  after the shot?  Or perhaps the effect was low blood sugar for which the ginger ale helped.

Client was vaccinated next to EMT ambulance due to prior allergic reactions and medical history. Approximately 3 minutes after vaccination, client reported onset of throat tightening and proceeded to progress to a full anaphylactic reaction, with stridor and respiratory distress.   At one minute after onset of symptoms, patient was administered 0.3 mL epinephrine IM in the left deltoid, and was transferred to a gurney and then into the rig, where oxygen was applied via non-rebreather mask at 12L/min, and vital signs were taken with  a HR of 96 and BP of 146/113.  Respirations were stridorous and approximately 40-60.  SaO2 after oxygen was high 90's.   Within the next 3-5 minutes, stridor lessened and client appeared more comfortable and gave a "thumbs up sign". IM Benadryl was given at approximately 8 minutes post onset.  A second transport ambulance from Medical Center was requested at onset of symptoms and arrived shortly after the dose of Benadryl.  Stridor was minimal and vital signs were HR 95, BP 123/78, with improved respirations, minimal stridor, no accessory muscle use and good air entry.  SaO2 was 100% on oxygen. IV attempt was unsuccessful by local EMT and patient was transferred to the second team for further care and transport to the Medical Center.
OTHER_MEDS: Lamotrigine and a second anti-seizure medication

SYMPTOM_TEXT: When the needle entered my arm, that felt normal. But I felt extreme pressure and immediate pain as soon as the plunger got depressed. I took Advil when I got home, and have taken it very 6 hours since, along with lots of water.  I have used a heating pad with some immediate relief but no improvement in the pain.  I am trying to stretch and move the arm, but am requiring assistance with even that because of how much pain is involved with simple movements.  It does not seem nerve related as it does not radiate down my arm.  The pain is isolated to my shoulder joint.

About 14 hours after receiving my second shot of the vaccine, I awoke being very cold and began to shiver and shake almost violently after getting out of bed to urinate.  Also my back, hips and knee joint were aching when I moved about any at all.  I was able to fall back to sleep and in the few time I awoke during the rest of the night, I didn't experience the shaking, however, with the aching and feeling cold, it was reminiscent of times when I had a fever.  Unfortunately, I do not have a working thermometer, so I could not check this, but I suspect I did have a fever.  I was also experiencing a sort of mental brain fog of confusion and lack of full consciousness (felt like I could not bring myself awake enough to do much of anything).   The following morning, I was barely able to become awake enough and clear headed enough to send an email to my boss about having to miss work.  Except to get out of bed for a short time to use the bathroom or get something to drink, I slept most of Friday until late afternoon.  Then I was slightly more coherent and was able to get more to drink and eat.  But still sleepy and went back to sleep. I awoke in a sweat (not experienced before this time) and felt a little clearer in my mind and not as achy.  Slept again later through the night, but continued to wake up in a sweat during the night.  Finally this morning when I awoke, I felt more normal again.

Ammonia inhalant was crushed and immediately placed under the patient's nose. The patient came back to consciousness approximately 30 seconds after passing out. Patient was asked what symptoms he felt leading up to passing out. He said that he suddenly felt dizzy and does not remember much after. Patient states that he did not eat breakfast prior to receiving the vaccine and has a history of not doing well with needles or vaccines. He states that he now feels completely fine, however, the patient was advised to stay 30 minutes for monitoring, and once he felt comfortable standing up, a nurse walked with him to the observation area. Patient was provided an ice pack for his forehead. Observation nurse was notified of the adverse event and is now monitoring the patient.

We had a member come back for her second dose of the Moderna vaccine. It was administered and she was given a timer to wait her 15 minutes. She turned in her timer at the end of the 15 minutes and told us she was leaving. A few minutes later she came back and stated that she was not feeling well. I told her to have a seat and went to check on her. She stated that she was having pain down her arm where she was given the vaccine and down her left side. Then she stated she was itching. I could see her starting to turn red with hives/rash on her left arm where we administered the vaccine. stayed with the patient in front of the pharmacy while I ran into the pharmacy and got the blood pressure machine, Benadryl, EpiPen, adverse reaction chart, and cold pack. I asked to grab pen and paper and take notes as we ran back out. Her itching was becoming more severe, and she stated she was feeling lightheaded. We immediately began checking her blood pressure (which was extremely high at 187/120) and administered 50 mg of Benadryl. We applied a cold pack to her neck as it appeared she was sweating and then applied a cold pack to the injection site. She continued to progress with the itching moving to other sites on her body. I asked one of the technicians to get the other pharmacist to call 911 and a code white was called.  She was in a chair without arms, and I needed to have her lay down. I also had five more people waiting for vaccine administration, so we moved her to the break room. We continued to monitor her blood pressure, which was dropping, and watch for signs of anaphylaxis. She stated she was feeling really tired and began closing her eyes. We continued to have her talk with us and not go to sleep. We had EpiPen's ready for administration if needed. The EMS arrived as we were checking her BP once again and they took over. She was placed on a stretcher and taken into the ambulance. Assistant had a curbside delivery a little while after the incident, at this point the EMS decided that her blood pressure had normalized, and the Benadryl was enough to control her allergic reaction and she was released to go home.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient had the injection, reported that is wasn't bad and then within a few minutes when in the waiting area, he reported feeling very light headed, nauseous, and lost his vision and hearing was fuzzy. He was cold and clammy. He never lost consciousness.  It took him a couple  minutes to "come back" to alertness and feel better.   Severe headache, chills starting and began asthma symptoms (wheezing) at 11;30pm the night of the injection.. 2 extra strength Tylenol did not help. He was very cold and the headache did not let up after several hours.  Eventually he had a bout of sweats and he reports he was soaked.  In the morning, at 8 am the headache was still severe...was sensitive to noise, light and touch. He was given 2 extra strength Tylenol at 8 and then 2 Advil at 10am, which finally began to reduce symptoms. He was not hungry, felt weak, and finally by late night he was feeling better.  In the morning on Saturday he awoke with a swollen left eye and blood shot in that eye.
ALLERGIES: Penicillin. Seasonal allergies. Allergic to animals.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient is a 43-year-old, male with a history of fear of needles. At 2:39 pm, the patient received a dose of the Janssen vaccine, (lot number 1808980, expires on 06/20/2021) on right deltoid, given by RN. Immediately following the vaccination at 2:40 pm, Patient reportedly slumped his head forward in his seat and was caught by RN, sustaining zero physical bodily injuries. The patient was unconscious for approximately 2 seconds. EMT'S responded immediately at 2:40 pm and took the patient's vitals. At 2:40 pm, the patients vitals were: 117 systolic BP and HR 89 (EMT unable to hear the diastolic BP due to environmental noise). The patient appeared diaphoretic, pale, with warm, clammy hands and a weak radial pulse. The patient was given a water and tolerated intake of water. The patient was assisted by EMT  to a anti-gravity chair at 2:43pm. The patient was observed to have a steady gait and reporting no dizziness. At 2:44 pm, the patient's vitals were: HR 54 and 110 systolic BP (EMT unable to hear the diastolic BP due to environmental noise). At 2:50, the patient had a strong, bounding radial pulse with a HR of 70 BPM and 115 systolic BP (EMT unable to hear the diastolic BP due to environmental noise). At 2:55 pm, the patient's vitals were: HR 75 BPM and 115 systolic BP (EMT unable to hear the diastolic BP due to environmental noise). At this time the patient reports feeling "better". At 3:00 pm the patient's vitals were: HR 81 BPM and 118 systolic BP (EMT unable to hear the diastolic BP due to environmental noise). At 3:05 pm the patient's vitals were: HR 77 BPM and 120 systolic BP (EMT unable to hear the diastolic BP due to environmental noise). At 3:10 pm the patient's vitals were: HR 74 BPM and 118 systolic BP (EMT unable to hear the diastolic BP due to environmental noise). At 3:15 pm, the patient was assisted up from anti-gravity chair. The patient had a steady and balanced gait. The patient denied any additional dizziness, lightheadedness, or nausea. EMT provided patient with education related to when to call his HCP (i.e. dizziness, itching of throat). The patient reported he was "ok to drive home" and left to the parking lot at 3:15 pm.
Severe nausea, vomiting, and chills for 5+ hours, NO FEVER
ALLERGIES: Allergies to fruit (mango, banana, lemon, apples, kiwi, avocado)

SYMPTOM_TEXT: HPI: Patient is a * year old * who presents following administration of a single dose of J&J COVID19 vaccine in the left deltoid.  About 20 minutes following administration of the vaccine, the patient started to experience numbness in the left shoulder to the left neck and post auricular region.  Patient denies allergies to medication, food, and other vaccines.  She states she has never had a similar experience.  She declares a past medical history of asthma that is controlled with rescue inhaler and oral medication.  She has not taken the medication for the past week and uses her rescue inhaler 2-3 times per week, particularly when she exercises or coughs too much.  She affirms numbness of the left neck, left shoulder, She denies chest pain, difficulty breathing, swelling of the face/lips/tongue/throat, skin rash/itching, cramping abdominal pain, nausea, and vomiting.     Exam (update as needed): GEN: Alert and oriented x 4, NAD. HEAD: NCAT EYES: PERRL, EOMI ENT: Decreased touch sensation in the left post auricular region and left posterior neck region.  Normal ROM and 5/5 strength of the neck. Right ear normal, Nose normal, OP normal, no evidence of angioedema NECK: Supple, without LAD.  CV: RRR, no m/r/g PULM: Clear to auscultation bilaterally, no accessory muscle use ABD: Soft, no tenderness. SKIN: No rashes, skin warm and dry.  No erythema or edema of the injection site. MSK: FROM of the bilateral upper extremities and neck, MS 5/5 bilaterally NEURO: Alert and oriented x 4, CN 2-12 grossly intact, no ataxia, gait steady.  Decreased sensation of the left post auricular region, left posterior neck region, left shoulder, left bicep compared to the contralateral side.   Clinical Impression/Field Tx: Possible peripheral nerve injury secondary to vaccine administration.  Patient not displaying active signs and symptoms of anaphylaxis.   Patient demonstrated ability to adequately control airway and secretions.  The patient was experiencing decreased sensation on the ipsilateral side of the vaccine site compared to the contralateral side.  Muscle strength was 5/5 bilaterally.  CN II-XII were grossly intact.  Patient offered further evaluation by EMS, however, patient declined as she has an appointment with her PCP on Monday and would prefer to address it there.   Instructed patient to consult their PCP regarding the post-vaccination reaction.  Patient states she has an appointment on Monday.  Patient instructed to go to emergency department should the area of decreased sensation increase in size or if they develop chest pain, difficulty breathing, difficulty swallowing, swelling of the face/lips/mouth/tongue/throat, or cramping abdominal pain with nausea/vomiting, as these are signs of possible anaphylaxis that requires immediate intervention.     Medications administered: None   Disposition:  Home
OTHER_MEDS: Ventolin Rescue Inhaler, Oral anti-inflammatory medication for asthma

Finally, I was somehow able to grab a towel and struggle to my bedroom and laid there numb for about 10 minutes.  This episode ended at about noon but for the rest of the day, I had to sleep on and off, it exhausted me to try and eat,  I had hot flashes, more dizziness, arm pain, and nausea. SYMPTOM_TEXT: On the morning after the second vaccine, I awoke with a bad headache. I was expecting something like this so I didn't worry about it.  Within a couple of hours, however, the headache began to include migraine-like visual disturbances primarily in the left eye field of vision.  The pain got worse.  I took Tylenol as I was advised not to take ibuprofen.  The headaches and visual disturbances continued intermittently for a couple of weeks.  (The headaches are still here at a low level.  The visual disturbances/flashes disappeared after 12 days.)  While I was having the migraine-like symptoms, after about two or three days, I developed additional visual problems in my left eye.  There was like a gray nebula of strands in my visual field.  I went to the ophthalmologist on 4/6/21, 10 days after the shot.  She diagnosed Posterior Vitreous Detachment (PVD).  While she knew of no mechanism for the vaccine to cause this, I am reporting this as the headaches, visual disturbances/flashes, and the PVD developed immediately after the second Pfizer shot, headache rolling into flashes rolling into PVD nebula.  The doc said this may or may not go away after a while.  We shall see.
LAB_DATA: Visit to Dr. on 4/6/21, full ophthalmological workup including tests and inspection after dilation.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: extremely ill; extreme fatigue; nausea; muscle aches; He is afraid she has COVID; have achy arm; This is a spontaneous report from a contactable consumer (patient reported herself). A 84-Year-old female patient received first dose of BNT162B2 (PFIZER-BIONTECH COVID-19 VACCINE, Formulation: Solution for injection, Batch/lot number: EL3949, NDC number: Unknown, Expiry Date: May2021) intramuscularly given very high in the top of left arm on 04Feb2021 9:20 AM at 0.3 ml single dose for Covid-19 immunization. The patient's medical history included fractured skull (five years ago), shingles (two years ago) and bleeding ulcers. Concomitant medications were not reported. Patient had the first dose of PFIZER-BIONTECH COVID-19 VACCINE last 04Feb2021 at 9:20 AM - Same day 6:00 PM started to have achy arm - After a few days developed symptoms like extremely ill, extreme fatigue, nausea, muscle aches. DSU potential duplicate AE Report E transmit - According to the patient she had already reported the side effects and transferred to our department. On 04Feb2021, the patient experienced arm started to ache like hell. Tiredness, muscle pain, nausea and feeling horribly ill. It was reported that, "she was having some symptoms. She got her vaccination on the 04Feb2021 and developed the symptoms yesterday. Her doctor was very alarmed that it was not just usual symptoms that go along with the vaccine because of the length of time between when she got it and when she developed symptoms. He was afraid she had COVID. She needed to know if that was normal so she could get back to him. Caller clarified that she meant side effects. She wanted to know whether it was normal to have gotten the vaccine on 04Feb2021 and not develop side effects until 09Feb2021. The vaccination was given in the morning at 9:20 AM and she did not have any symptoms until 6:00 PM that evening. Her arm started to ache like hell. That one showed up then, but cleared up in a couple of days. The arm got better and better. The other set of side effects started yesterday which was tiredness, muscle pain, nausea, and feeling horribly ill. She felt awful and did not want to go to a hospital if it was not necessary. HCP information included she had only seen him a couple of times. She had a long term doctor that retired and she got shifted over to him. They did not have a good relationship she must say. His whole group was associated with where she got the vaccine. They were all virtual now. She had been on lock down for a year. She did not have the doctor's address, phone number, or email. Tiredness, muscle pain, nausea, and feeling horribly ill: started yesterday morning when she got up between 4:30 AM and 5:00 AM. She was so woozy and thought it was left over sleep. She felt unwell all day. She had felt unwell today, but not as bad as yesterday. She had to get vaccination card out of hand bag and needs her glasses to read the small numbers. First dose was given on 04Feb2021. She had appointment on 25Feb2021 for second dose. Healthcare Provider who gave the vaccine was Hospital. They called her on the third at 5:00 PM to see if she could come the next day for the vaccine. They did a good job. Her brother was a retired anesthesiology and she called him this morning and he said to go to the hospital or testing center. Then he agreed that she should call Pfizer. History of all previous immunization with the Pfizer vaccine considered as suspect and additional vaccines administered on same date of the Pfizer suspect were none. She did not get her flu shot in anticipation of getting the COVID vaccine. Her brother and his granddaughter were both anesthesiologist. They get work up about not being able to breathe and ventilators. They gave advice. She was glad her brother approved for her to call Pfizer to find out. She wanted to believe it was side effects. She had been on lock down. Her brother said she could have been exposed at the vaccine site. Caller stated everyone had on a mask. She was not obese. She was not sure if it is relevant, but she would tell it anyway. She fractured her skull 5 years ago and was in Hospital because it was bleeding. That had resolved. She was in ICU and then six weeks of acute rehab. She had a bad case of shingles two years ago which led to bleeding ulcers. Again she went to the hospital, but she was scoped they found ulcers and treated. She went back for scope again and it had all healed up". Outcome of the event have achy arm was recovering whereas other events was unknown.
HISTORY: Medical History/Concurrent Conditions: Shingles (She had a bad case of shingles two years ago which led to bleeding ulcers); Skull fracture (fractured her skull 5 yrs ago and was in Hospital because it was bleeding/that had resolved); Ulcer bleeding (She had a bad case of shingles two years ago which led to bleeding ulcers)

SYMPTOM_TEXT: headaches; pretty serious muscle aches; projectile vomiting; fever; chills; massive diarrhea; tiredness; This is a spontaneous report from a contactable consumer (patient). The patient medical history were not reported and no concomitant medications. The patient did not receive any other vaccines within 4 weeks prior to the COVID vaccine. AE following prior vaccinations was reported as none. Vaccination facility type was reported as hospital and not a military facility. The patient called for information about if her symptoms could be related to the administration of the Pfizer's COVID-19 vaccine. The patient reported that she has massive diarrhea (08:30), projectile vomiting (10:00), fever (10:00), pretty serious muscle aches (11:00), tiredness (07:30), headache (13:00) and chills (08:30) on 10Feb2021. Events fever, Pretty serious muscle aches and tiredness were reported as worsened. The patient reported that she was administered with the first dose of the vaccine 2 weeks ago and she was feeling fine starting with the symptoms today (10Feb2021). The patient reported that she thought it was possible that she has been infected of COVID-19 virus. The patient reported that she considered herself a healthy 79-year-old woman. Received call from the patient regarding the Pfizer COVID 19 vaccine. She had the first vaccine two weeks ago today (10Feb2021). She was having massive Diarrhea, Chills, projectile vomiting, fatigue, muscle aches and fever.  She started out with her normal body temp of 97.3 and this morning it was 98.2.  She took it an hour later, and it was 98.4 and then it was 100 and now it was 100.2.  That was why she was calling.  She would like to know if these were side effects. She said she cannot think. She filled out two forms on the second day after the shot. It came up on her email and it listed the symptoms and said have you had any today.  She was kind of fatigued today (10Feb2021). A week later she had pretty serious muscle aches and one more thing. The diarrhea was one massive one this morning and it got rid of everything. It was liquid. She has not had one since. She slept most of the time straight chair. Sciatica was better, but not gone. Day 9, she walked outside, temp was normal. She was sent for flu & Covid tests (nasal swab), both negative. She also mentioned something else IV but did not know the name of it. The patient was also taking levosalbutamol hydrochloride (XOPENEX) as treatment. She was still having problems with itching. She was still really itchy. She asked when this stuff would clear out of her system. She had been taking diphenhydramine to calm down. She was constantly scratching. She took diphenhydramine and used her rescue inhaler. She had her inhaler, but she keeps itching. She carried an epinephrine (EPIPEN) and now she was having trouble with her breathing and she was trying to rest. Outcome of the rash and wheezing was unknown while of the remaining events was not recovered.  The following information on the batch number has been requested.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: she doesn't have a taste for food; difficulty breathing; Fever; Headache; joint aches like when you have the flu and muscles aching; joint aches like when you have the flu and muscles aching; Stomach was very upset- she had a queasy feeling and she could hardly get anything down like when you have the flu and no taste for anything; Felt like she had the flu; weak and fatigued- didn't have energy to do her dishes; weak and fatigued- didn't have energy to do her dishes/tired; her nerves and nervous system were being affected- nerves were feeling funny; felt miserable; heart was beating faster; Chills- she could not get warm; Coughing; This is a spontaneous report from a contactable consumer (patient). A female patient of an unspecified age received BNT162B2 (PFIZER-BIONTECH COVID-19 VACCINE, lot number: ER2613, expiration date unknown), via an unspecified route of administration on 19Mar2021 at 08:30 AM at a single dose for COVID-19 immunisation. Medical history included ongoing arthritis in left hip, ongoing high blood pressure and Cholesterol. Concomitant medications included atenolol, orally, at 10 mg, once a day (Takes 1/2 a pill for 10mg) for high blood pressure, ATORVASTATIN, orally, at 5 mg, as needed (once a day at night (7:30 to 8p), by mouth, as needed) for Cholesterol and beet extract (takes a piece of a pill, exact dose unknown). The patient reported she received the Pfizer Covid shot last Friday (19Mar2021) and had a very bad reaction. Patient stated that her reaction was not immediately, she waited there for fifteen minutes after the shot and did not have a reaction then. Patient stated that when she left, she went shopping because she needed some groceries and the shot affected her nervous system. Patient reported that about an hour after the shot, her nerves were feel-ing funny, she kept moving and shopping. Stated that her nerves to play tricks on her sometimes, so she just tries to ignore it. When she got home, her nervous system wasn't being affected anymore. Patient clarified this lasted for about two hours. Patient reported that on Saturday morning, 20Mar2021, she had a fever and a headache, then she had joint aches and muscle aches and her stomach was upset. She felt like she had the flu. Patient mentioned that she was perfectly healthy before she had the shot. Stated she doesn't know if they let that Pfizer shot sit out too long or what. A question was asked to the patient, is there a chance that if they left it out too long that it could cause a reaction like this? Patient mentioned that she was supposed to get the vaccine at 8:30; she got there at quarter after 8 (8:15 am) and she had four pages to fill out. Patient stated that she doesn't know how long they had it out for, but she thinks they would be more conscientious about it because Pfizer's vaccine is more temperamental when it comes to the temperatures. Stated that she called and left her phone number at the hospital, but nobody called her back so she doesn't know what that means. Patient stated that she can't explain why she had such a bad reaction. Patient reported that for about two to three days, she had chills and a fever for two days, a headache, joint aches like when you have the flu and her muscles were aching, stomach was very upset- she could hardly get anything down, like when you have the flu and have no taste for anything and stomach is queasy, was weak and fatigued, but she noticed that this didn't last very long. Patient reported this also affected her breathing, she had difficulty breathing for a couple days (for about a day and half), her heart was also beating faster for a couple days. Patient stated that she is not the kind of person who babies herself. Patient reported she laid around Saturday and Sunday because she did not have any energy at all and felt miserable. On Monday, 22Mar2021, her stomach was still queasy and she still had the chills, she could not get warm. Caller stated that she tried not to think about her aches and pains and to be more normal, it was hard but it helped her feel better. Patient reiterated she walked in there very healthy and after she got the shot, it hit her pretty hard. Patient reported that she was not up to her usual energy level still and doesn't have any real craving for food, she forces herself to eat and she doesn't let herself starve, but she doesn't have a taste for food. Patient mentioned that she was kind of craving sweets and thinks it was because she's still kind of tired. Patient stated that she forced herself to clean the living room and vacuumed because she wanted to push herself to keep her muscles moving. Patient explained that she was not going to sit around and feel sorry herself because the more you feel sorry for yourself, the worse you feel. Patient reported that the muscle and joint aches have gone away and she was coughing a little bit, but it's not real hard. Patient reported that it was taking her almost a week to recuperate. Patient does not know if she wanted to get another shot because her reaction was so bad. Patient was scheduled to get her next shot on 09Apr2021. Patient mentioned that she knows that everyone reacts a little differently, but she had never reacted this severely to a shot before. Patient reported she just hopes that she plans to go for a walk and needs to keep herself moving and keep herself healthy. Patient stated that she usually walks three miles, but didn't have the strength to go for a long walk and she's going to push herself today and go for a longer walk before it starts snowing or raining. Patient clarified she has not walked all week and she usually goes for a walk everyday. Patient stated that she was retired. Patient mentioned that she likes to keep moving and hopes to lift some weights to get her strength back. Patient stated that it started affecting her nerves in the afternoon when she got the shot, but when she got up on saturday, she was really sick with the other symptoms. Patient reported that she put gloves on hands because she was so cold. She had three layers on and she was still freezing so she laid down. Patient stated that when you are sick, you need to lay down and take care of your body and let it fight the infection. Patient reported that she didn't have energy to do her dishes. Patient stated that she has been eating yogurt so she can keep it down and not get her stomach upset. Patient stated that she was still not completely recovered, she was still tired and it may take a half a week to get back to normal. Patient mentioned that she doesn't like to sit around and feel sick. Patient reported that she does get headaches from time to time, but she stopped experiencing the headaches from the shot. Patient took some ibuprofen as treatment and laid down. She stated that she noticed she still had the muscles aches on monday, but she kept trying to strengthen them. Patient mentioned she had not tried picking up her weights- they are only 5 pounds, they are not very heavy, but it takes a while for muscles to get back into shape and she doesn't want to strain them. Patient reported she was normally a high energy person, but she just doesn't have that energy right now and the shot took a lot out of her. Patient mentioned that she just didn't know if she could keep anything down. She had cheese and crackers for breakfast because they are comforting to your stomach. She also had yogurt in the afternoon to coat her stomach. Outcome for upset stomach: Patient stated that it improved a little, but she is still queasy. She takes tums at night so it doesn't bother her. She still can't eat anything she wanted. Patient mentioned she made a Salmon chowder with crackers and she could keep some of that down. Patient explained it has Salmon, milk, potatoes in it and she put a little bit of dried parsley in it because parsley is good for digestion and it soothes the stomach. Patient stated that she feels like she is slowly getting over the flu; she was still not 100%, but she would try getting up and walking. She also mentioned that she was just a little more tired than she was before and is trying to build up the strength and endurance to get back into shape. Stated that she started feeling weak and fatigued the day of the shot; she went to bed early that night. Stated that she was really busy yesterday, but still felt really tired. She just kept going because she didn't want to feel sorry for herself. Outcome for Difficulty Breathing: Patient reported she opened some windows because the cold air is good for you and that helped. Patient clarified she did not have any breathing problems before. Also stated that she was really scared when her heart was racing. She explained that after the initial feeling of the flu, she felt her heart was beating faster, she had never felt that before and felt like that had to be from the shot. She does not know what day the heart racing began, but reported it started on either 21Mar2021, 22Mar2021, or 23Mar2021. She described the heart racing as an after effect. She reported that it took about two or three days for her heart to stop racing, it lasted longer than the breathing problems. She reiterated that she was not sure at this point if she was going to get another shot because of the reaction she had, she still had to think about it. She wondered if it affected her heart. She also mentioned that she doesn't like to be sick or handicapped, she hopes she can recover completely. At this point, she wanted to keep pushing herself to getting back to regular exercise, she was trying to get back to normal and lead a normal life. She reported she was so healthy before she got the shot and never expected to have this kind of reaction. Outcome for heart is beating faster: Reported that her heart wasn't beating faster right now, but she doesn't know if her heart was weakened until she pushes herself when she started exercising again. Patient stated that it was being offered and they are recommending people who are older-get it to prevent covid 19. She stated that she's been healthy and thinks she has a natural immunity to flu and the virus. She stated that she goes out shopping to get her own groceries and tries to keep the six feet distance and wears masks. Arthritis- She stated that she did cross guarding and didn't dress warm enough. Blood Pressure: Patient stated that last time her blood pressure was 120/72 or 120/70. She does not not really have high blood pressure anymore. Caller states she did have high blood pressure a little bit, but she supposes it was from when she was under a lot of stress. The patient recovered from her nerves and nervous system were being affected- nerves were feeling funny on 19Mar2021, recovered from fever, joint aches like when you have the flu and muscles aching on 22Mar2021, recovered from headache, difficulty breathing on 21Mar2021, recovered from heart was beating faster on an unspecified date in Mar2021, outcome for chills, coughing, she doesn't have a taste for food was unknown and for other events outcome was recovering.  Follow-up attempts are completed. No further information is expected.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: feels like he might be getting the flu; pain in stomach; headache; anything he eats turns to acid; This is a spontaneous report from a contactable consumer (patient). Medical history included ongoing sarcoidosis he has had for at least 35 years, oozing leg from 2019 and "underlying health issues". He had bloodwork done 3 times and it came back negative for COVID-19: he had one done in Mar2020, one done in Jun2020, and one done three months before this report (Dec2020). Historical vaccine included flu shot in Sep2020 or Oct2020 with no problem and he gets it every year. Concomitant medications included olmesartan/hydrochlorothiazide 40 mg/25mg tablets from 2019 and ongoing for blood pressure; amlodipine from 2019 and ongoing for blood pressure abnormal; oxybutynin for incontinence ("to control his bladder so that he does not have to go"), from an unknown date, almost one year before this report (2020) and ongoing; colchicine (COLCRYS) (not actually taking it as he is out of it), from the middle of Feb2021 for gout; allopurinol from the middle of Feb2021 and ongoing for gout; calcium carbonate (ACID BREAKTHROUGH FORMULA) for antacid therapy, from an unknown date and ongoing ("has been taking it on and off for 20 years"); ibuprofen, taking on and off for the last 5 years (now ongoing) for pain, from an unknown date; ascorbic acid (VITAMIN C ACID) from an unknown date (has been on at least the last 4 years) for cold or flu prophylaxis; ongoing fish oil (has been on for the last 2 or 3 years) for blood cholesterol (he was told it was supposed to help cholesterol), from an unknown date and metformin for pre-diabetes ("his numbers are very low, but they told him to take it so that he does not get diabetes"), from an unknown date (has been on it for about a year and a half). Past drug history included oxycodone-acetaminophen, which was last filled on 03Oct2011. In Mar2021, two weeks after the first dose of BNT162B2 Pfizer-BioNTech COVID-19 Vaccine he did not feel the best: he felt fine the first week, but then, on "Sunday" [21Mar2021] the patient felt like he might be getting the flu, he experienced pain in stomach, stating that the pain is there but it does not hurt that bad, headache, defined as "not that bad, just a mild headache; it is about the same, it is an annoying ache", and anything he eats turns to acid. The events didn't require ED or physician office visit. The patient added that there is a problem with his leg where it is oozing, started two years before this report, and they are going to give him antibiotics, cephalexin 500 mg capsule. His second vaccine dose is planned on 31Mar2021 and he is afraid that antibiotics could interfere with the vaccine efficacy. The patient didn't receive any treatment, as he thought that this would just go away in 2 to 3 days. At the time of the report the stomach pain was ongoing ("it goes and comes"), as well as the event "anything he eats turns to acid"; the outcome of the other events was unknown.

Janssen COVID-19 Vaccine EUA  I received the Janssen vaccine in my upper-left arm at 3:00 PM on April 5, 2021, at a public health clinic (I think that's the proper term for the site) established in a mall. After about ten minutes, during the scheduled waiting period, I began to feel lightheaded; I can best compare the feeling to that of being tipsy after a glass or two of wine. I waited another twenty minutes at the site to see if the feeling worsened, and when it didn't, I left without telling anyone how I felt. During the drive home, however, I continued to feel lightheaded during the drive home and worried that it might be affecting my driving. After I got home without incident, the feeling persisted for a few hours and ceased that evening.  Since then, I have experienced nothing but what I think are standard post-vaccination symptoms (fatigue, muscle aches, slight brain fog, swollen lymph nodes?not unlike the sensations of recovering from a modest cold). I nevertheless want to report the lightheadedness because it appears (based on news reports) that it is an unusual reaction to the vaccine. SYMPTOM_TEXT: Janssen COVID-19 Vaccine  Chills, muscle aches, mild headache, a sudden reduced ability to hear and see, cold sweat, lightheadedness, disorientation  Starting at approximately 1:00 am on 4/08/21 I woke up with a throbbing left arm, muscle aches, a very mild headache, and chills accompanied by bouts of uncontrollable shivering.  I experienced these cold like symptoms throughout the night.  At around 6:00 am, I woke up with a very mild headache and muscle aches.   I took my temperature, and had a 101 degree Fahrenheit fever. I rested, and took my temperature multiple times that morning-- which had been gradually decreasing. At around 11:30/12:00 I experienced a sudden onset of extreme fatigue followed closely by a greatly reduced ability to hear and see, along with extreme lightheadedness and the feeling like I was going to pass out. I suddenly became cold, and my body was drenched in sweat in a matter of seconds.  I think the whole experience lasted around 10 minutes, before it eventually began to pass. I could see clearly again  and began to regain my hearing, however I still experienced some lingering auditory complications for an additional three- five minutes ( it sounded like a throbbing white noise). After that, I felt a little disoriented and tired. My aunt had taken me to Urgent Care, but they turned me away, saying I needed to go to the ER. However, by that time my symptoms had passed and I was feeling ok. So I went home and rested. By the next morning, I felt I had completely recovered

The night after my first vaccine, I awoke at about 3:45AM with extreme aches and pains all over my body for about 4 hours, then I was okay.  Twelve days later, I tried to go for a short walk with my wife and the pain in my left leg was horrible at times.  The calf muscle was swollen and pink and very warm to the touch.  Also my toes were kind of purple and my ankles were badly swollen.  I thought the toes and ankles might be related to my Bradycardia, but the calf muscle sent us to the ER to be checked for a blood clot.  They did check the major arteries, as those are the dangerous ones, but did not check the calf as they said if one was there it wouldn't throw to the lungs or heart.  I was discharged.  The swelling went down in the calf.  Still some aches in the back of both legs now when I walk very far - but really not bad.  Having the purple toes and a possible blood clot... my daughter who is a nurse encouraged me to submit this information.  Thank you.
LAB_DATA: 3/30/2021 Ultra-sound on main arteries showed to be clear.
OTHER_MEDS: Zoloft, Lunesta, Atorvastatin, Baby Aspirin, Vitamin C, D, and Multivitamin, Claritin, Omeprazole,

Patient  is not on any  medications at this time and only has a history of an ovarian cyst. Patient denies any allergies and  no known drug allergies.  Patient was transfered  over from  the chair to a wheel chair by standing and pivoting . Patient was then brought to a  back hallway 100ft  away  to be  further evaluated.  Patient blood pressure was 120/90, heart rate 80, spo2 99%. Patient was put on oxygen via nasal cannula  at 4lpm.  Patients said her breathing  started to improve.  Patient then started to say her throat was feeling dry and described a lump forming in her throat. Patient had sip of water to see if she could swallow.  Respiratory rate increased  to hyperventilating  40 breaths per minute.  Vitals were attempted to be reassessed, but then the patient began to experience nausea and dry heaving.  At this time  a paramedic  who is administering vaccinations  to patients stepped in  to help administer epinephrine 1:1,000 .3mg  intramuscular on the left thigh. Providence Fire/Rescue showed up  and patient was then transferred from wheel chair to  Providence Fire/Rescue stretcher with 2 EMT limb lift. Patient was then put on a Non-Rebreather at 15lpm of oxygen. Patient care was transferred over to Providence Fire/Rescue.  Personnel on Providence  Fire/Rescue names were not obtained and no signature was obtained.

I should point out that I donated a pint of blood 2 hours before getting my Moderna shot. I thought it would 27 hours before the shot but after donating the pharmacy called and said they had vaccine available if we wanted to move  up getting our shots right then 24 hours before our appointment.  8 hours later,  at 3:00am I got up to go to the bathroom. I immediately started feeling nauseous and light headed. I ended up collapsing and falling flat on my back. I immediately started shivering and shaking along with the nausea. For the next 12 hours I was extremely weak and my joints severely ached. It was very hard to move.   The total experience lasted roughly 18 hours before I started feeling significantly better.  Before donating blood I asked the if getting the Moderna Covid shot 27 hours (I thought 27 hours at that time) after donating would be a problem .  They said no. We asked the pharmacist before getting the shot if donating blood 2 hours earlier would be a problem. She thought naught and said she had no guidance against it.  I?m a very very healthy 67 year old. I rarely get sick and I have no prescriptions.  Complicating my blood donation was that my pulse was 44 beats per minute but my good health allowed them to proceed.  I?m not complaining about anyone or anything. I just thought you should be advised of my experience.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Approximated 12-13 minutes after receiving the shot; my respiration increased, heart rate, and my vision became blurred.  I reported the blurred vision to the Pharmacist and she said they have not heard reports forth this symptom.  Based upon events following the injection relative to my blood pressure; it is likely that my blood pressure became elevated following the injection, resulting in blurred vision.  My blurred vision   resolved several minutes later.  However, my heart rate increased later that evening to the point I slept upright in my recliner that evening.  During sleep, I awoke from my sleep gasping because my heart felt like it was beating too slowly.  It has not been several weeks since receiving the injection, and during this time period, my Blood Pressure (BP) has been fluctuating from "very high" to normal.  Yesterday, I presented to the ER due to High Blood Pressure (145/100), by the recommendation of a NP.   I have NEVER had any history of high BP prior to the injection.
LAB_DATA: The EKG report on April 9, 2021 found that there is a slight delay in blood flow to ventricles and the electrical current for the heart is not as strong as it should be.  The Plan is weight loss, exercise, and follow-up with PCP.  Although I am overweight for my age and height (within last year weight gain), I am concerned how sporadic my BP has become since receiving the vaccine on March 12, 2021.

After a few hours, developed a low grade headache and some soreness at the injection site.  About two hours later I started getting extremely cold, despite the temperature in the mid-high 70s. I covered up under blankets. I began feeling very tired and a general sick feeling. After about an hour and a half of progressively worse chills and cold sweat, I began to get very very hot and removed all blankets and eventually clothes. I took my temperature, which was at 102 f. At this point I drank some water and Gatorade and waited for it to pass. I also noticed that my Apple Watch heart rate detection was saying my heart rate was in the high 90s to low 100s despite me just laying in bed. This was alarming because my typical resting heart rate is in the low 60s. About two hours later I felt well enough to at least brush my teeth, but upon standing up was greeted with an extreme feeling of weakness and dizziness and it was hard to keep myself up right. I eventually was able to fall asleep, and upon waking up, felt better, but still not great. My heart rate was more normal at this point, I no longer had chills or a fever, but still had a headache and soreness across my body, worst at the injection site.

As the day went on, everything got worse. Any time I moved, my head would throb so bad that I thought I was going to have to go to the hospital.   3:45 pm:  the headache started to finally go away. It would only hurt if I moved fast. At this point my fever was only slightly high, about 99 degrees. I was still unstable when I walked and dizzy. Saturday 4/10: 7:00am: woke up with a slight headache; still out of it and dizzy.   8:00am: after being awake for about an hour or so, I looked in the mirror and my whole face (around the lips, cheeks, and jawline, and under the eyes) was really swollen and puffy. I am 77.  I had the Pfizer vaccine, March 9th,  with a terrible reaction starting 2 days after.  I couldn't use my brain to think, to read with comprehension, to remember things I wanted to remember and had difficulty finding my words. This lasted for 3 days when the fog began to lift.  I also had some shortness of breath(SOB)  and very low energy.  The CDC has said that when giving the injection it is no longer necessary to aspirate (pull back on the syringe) which I was taught to do as a young nurse to ensure that you are not giving the injection into a vein (blood would appear in the syringe.) It is supposed to be given into the muscle which has plenty of veins so if you don't aspirate, how will you know if you are injecting into a vein? A week later, I ended up going to the local hospital ER because of the SOB and had Chest xray, EKG, brain Cat Scan and blood work which were all normal. I debated about getting the second shot but decided to get it as long as the injector gave the injection as I had been taught. Fortunately she was very experienced and agreed to inject me using the pullback method after I explained what I had gone through the 1st time. So for the second shot I had the sore arm but no other reaction. I think Dr is making a mistake about the pullback decision.  Do we even know what happens if the vaccine is injected into a vein? I am not certain if my first shot was injected into a vein because the injector never pulled back to check.  I have not heard of anyone else with my experience.
LAB_DATA: 03/16/2021  Tests: EKG, Chest xray, Brain cat scan, various blood work .  Doctor at ER at reported                      that all tests were normal which was one week after 1st shot.
OTHER_MEDS: NP Thyroid 97.5 mg Bystolic 5 mg numerourous vitamun supplements

The morning after I woke up, I had intense abdominal cramping. The cramping was high in the gut area. I figured it was an adverse side effect. The cramping did not subsist night or day and the intensity was great. I called my GI on Monday and got an appointment. When I saw him, he ordered a CT scan and put me on a strong antibiotic thinking that it was an infection, not related to the vaccine. Meanwhile I had a CT scan and blood workup. The CT scan came back with significant swelling and inflammation in my small intestines. Five miserable days later my GI took me off of the antibiotic and was now talking about putting my on a strong steroid. (Budesonide) Then, due to tremendous cramping I went to the ER where they did another CT Scan, blood workup as well. They did see less swelling and that gave us hope that the steroid was working. Finally, I got a endoscopy where they took six biopsies. We are still waiting on the biopsies but they doctor said the inflammation was going done but that my stomach lining was particularly red. That is where it stands today just past one month. The pain is going down but both of my healthcare professionals are warned me against getting the second dose of the vaccine. They are both convinces this is a rare type of allergic reaction to the vaccine.
LAB_DATA: 2  - CT Scans done 2 - Blood work ups 1 - Endoscopy with 6 biopsies done on 4/6/21.
